          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLOHJfDBR-Bd1LNqbhd-doV3UeuFEuIQ3sqtYypeb-cZwUJ_d8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My appointment was years ago, but it\u2019s something that really stuck with me. After this visit, I actually avoided going to the dentist for a while because of how uncomfortable the experience was.\n\nThey recommended a very aggressive and costly treatment plan\u2014removing teeth, even though they were healthy, just because my tooth had been previously chipped and composite bonded. I came in inquiring about the discoloration .They immediately started talking about implants as the first option.\n\nThe first dentist explained the plan, but when I pushed back, they brought in another dentist who came off as very aggressive. The whole situation became overwhelming and emotional, and it didn\u2019t feel like they cared. The focus shifted to costs, insurance, and even suggesting I apply for a loan, which felt really predatory.\n\nAt one point, I overheard them doing something similar with another patient in the next room\u2014she was literally on the phone applying for a dental loan while they stood over her.\n\nI ended up getting a second opinion, and that dentist was surprised by how extreme the original treatment plan was.",
